summary: This is an FBI ELSUR (Electronic Surveillance) evidence envelope form documenting the chain of custody for an intercept. It indicates a consensual monitoring intercept took place on January 31, 2003, and the evidence was transferred for permanent storage on an unspecified date.

events.title: Consensual Monitoring Intercept
events.description: An electronic surveillance intercept was conducted, likely a telephonic consensual monitoring (TCM). The evidence was logged into an ELSUR evidence envelope.

keyFacts: The document is an FBI ELSUR evidence envelope form used to track chain of custody for intercepted communications.
It records a consensual monitoring intercept that occurred on January 31, 2003.
The form includes fields for case number, agent, supervising agent, intercept type, date, time, and signatures for chain of custody transfers.
The evidence was transferred for permanent storage, though the specific transfer date is not clearly legible in the provided text.
